</body></html>
</div><p class='maxread center'><a href="https://amonglegends519.bandcamp.com/album/the-worst-noel-a-punk-rock-holiday-benefit-ep" class="black no-underline fw4 db tc f6 nt3 mb4" target="_blank">Listen: Among Legends - <em>The Worst Noel: A Punk Rock Holiday Benefit EP</em> @ Bandcamp</a></p><p class='maxread center'>Red Deer punks <a href="https://highenddenimrecords.bandcamp.com/album/shout-at-the-nickel" class="black no-underline fw4 bb b--black" target="_blank">Burning Nickels</a> got in on the holiday action with <em>Cool Tide Carrolls</em>, a two-song set pairing their new original &quot;Rum Nogs&quot; with a cover of Roger Miller&#39;s &quot;Old Toy Trains.&quot;</p><p class='maxread center'>The single arrives right on the heels of <em>Bernie Goes To College</em>, the band&#39;s new five-song EP on <a href="http://highenddenimrecords.bandcamp.com" class="black no-underline fw4 bb b--black" target="_blank">High End Denim</a>. Burning Nickels features Josh (Jawsh) Hauta on guitar and Jason (Ozone) Ezeard drumming (both from <a href="https://trashedambulance.bandcamp.com/" class="black no-underline fw4 bb b--black" target="_blank">Trashed Ambulance</a>), with Robbie of Calgary punk act <a href="https://hickcitymorons.com/" class="black no-underline fw4 bb b--black" target="_blank">Moröns</a> on bass. <a href="https://bradmanners.bandcamp.com" class="black no-underline fw4 bb b--black" target="_blank">Brad Manners</a>, of Toronto&#39;s <a href="https://schooldamage.bandcamp.com/" class="black no-underline fw4 bb b--black" target="_blank">School Damage</a>, appears here as a guest vocalist.</p><div class='center tc media'><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
